description:
• Handling the escalation for all IT related issues (Incident/ Problem/Change). 
• Point of contact for all Major Incidents 
• Monitor the incidents to ensure that the Service Level Agreement are respected 
• Responsible for communicating with the Incident Process Owner 
• Ensure the closure of all resolved and end-user confirmed Incident records 
• Producing management information and reports 
• Ensuring that all IT teams follow the incident management process for every incident

• Linking the escalation task with incident problem records, identifying suitable service provider contacts, and finding the appropriate customer management services qualified for the task. 
• Initiating hierarchical escalation process as per the incident management process, including senior authorities and asking for their support, if the need arises 
• Updating and maintaining escalation process records at each stage, updating the same in management data, and reviewing and adjusting the escalation process accordingly 
• Worked on bouncing tickets to reduce the count of bounced incidents. 
• Providing contact details of Service Desk to the user so that they proceed accordingly as per their issues. 
• Several bouncing tickets are closed with our intervention.

title: Product Coordinator & Analyst
description:
At Fingent, we believe that what we build touches the lives around us. We use technology to create a better and smarter environment. We nurture thought leaders and encourage them to be the seeds of change through smart software development and consulting services. Our commitment to quality and integrity helps us to use technology and create a better and smarter future.

Skill Sets :
Proficiency in English.
Excellent oral and written communication skills.
Good interpersonal and team working skills with a passion to learn.
Detail-oriented with good attention to detail.
Customer-oriented and cool-tempered, ability to engage and connect with customers, have meaningful conversations, and nurture the relationship.
Programming/technical experience or good understanding of technology.
Experience in handling presentations and demos to customers/stakeholders.
Experience in collaborating and closely working with Development/Engineering teams.
Strong problem-solving and analytical skills. An interest in producing creative solutions.
Ability to manage multiple competing priorities in a fast-paced environment and deliver results.
Knowledge or exposure to Business Management will be an added advantage.

Roles & Responsibilities :
Product Expertise: Develop a sound knowledge of a complex and evolving software product; be well versed in all its features and capabilities. Ability to manage product demonstrations to internal/external audiences when required.
Requirements Detailing and Documentation: Conceptualize user scenarios, and capture these as workflows and wireframes. Define business use cases and success criteria for new features.
Product Coordination & Sprint Execution: Planning, Tracking, Execution, and Delivery of Sprints. Support and collaborate with the Engineering team in Product Backlog Grooming, Feature discussions, Mockup Reviews, UAT.
User Experience Research: Interview existing customers and/or potential users to get their feedback on the product. Collaborate with the Customer Support Team to gather customer insights and guide them on feature-related queries when required.
Inter-Department Coordination: Coordination and close collaboration with other internal product teams. Enable product upgrades and feature releases by liaising with Product Marketing, Sales, and Customer Support teams. Work closely with the Development team to understand how features are implemented.

More Information:

title: Power BI Developer
description:
At Fingent, we believe that technology can make a meaningful difference to the lives around us. The lives of those who use it, the lives of those who build it and to society at large. We create and provide software which is beautiful, usable and compelling, to solve complex business challenges. We nurture smart people who bring out the best in themselves, their peers and their clients.

Skill Set:

3 to 4 years of experience working with a self-service tool, preferably Power BI.
Experience of in data preparation, data gateway and data warehousing projects.
Should be experienced and familiar with other Business Intelligence analytical tools, such as SSRS, SSAS, and SSIS.
Must have experience in JavaScript and SQL Scripting.
Should be familiar in Ms SQL Server.
Must have experience with Business intelligence tools like Power BI.
Writing DAX expressions/queries BI stack knowledge, data analytics, and software development skills.
Dashboard making, creating reports, datasets analysing, and organization of the BI tools.
Familiarity with JavaScript, CSS, and other JavaScript libraries.

Roles and Responsibilities:


Building and maintaining analysis service report models.
Using Power BI Desktop for developing dashboards, visual reports, and key performance indicator (KPI) scorecards.
Extracting various data sources and connecting, importing, and transforming data for Business Intelligence.
Implementing row-level security on data.
Should be capable of understanding the application security layer model.
Must be capable of handling project documentation and design methodology.
Scheduling, developing, and publishing Power BI reports as per requirements.
Proficient in creating Data Analysis Expression (DAX) queries in Power BI Desktop.
Should be capable of developing multidimensional models that are compatible with warehouse standards.
Must be capable of understanding business requirements and data models while taking care of the sources.
Proficient in prototyping, designing, and requirement analysis.
Should have good knowledge of secondary tools, such as SQL Data Warehouse, Azure, Visual Studio, PolyBase, etc.
Implementing advanced-level calculations on datasets.
Understanding data with filters and graphs makes things easier.
Working with team members for the overall growth of the organization.

More Information:

Experience: 3-4 Years
Work Location: Kochi
